pr_body:
Consider...

```python
import pysodium as libnacl
class ED25519Identity(object):
    def __init__(self, pk = False, sk = False):
        if not sk:
            pk, sk = libnacl.crypto_sign_keypair()
        elif sk and not pk:
            pk = libnacl.crypto_sign_sk_to_pk(sk) # this PR adds this

        self.publickey = pk
        self.secretkey = sk
```

This very useful function was missing before.

Given that the previous code was returning a tuple while `close` expects a an int, I believe @roidelapluie 's fix should also be applied to python 2.
I guess it's just a part of the code we never hit before.
@jrief are you ok with this ?

several changes:

- changed std::to_string() to internal to_string();
- added iOS flags in cmakelists;
- C style typedef in zlib;
- added transparency and other attributes handling in glTF 1.0;
- added buffered embedded texture support in glTF 2.0;
- added missing pbrmaterial.h in installed headers.

Trying to remove GTable from the dx-toolkit helpstrings (all mentions of GTables on this page https://wiki.dnanexus.com/Command-Line-Client/Index%20of%20dx%20Commands). 

First commit in this branch just changed the helpstrings. Second commit attempts to remove the entire section of gtable-specific options from `dx head`. Not sure if removing the arguments from argparse is enough in this case ..

